Find (perhaps cite):

A.L. Delcher, A. Phillippy, J. Carlton, S.L. Salzberg, Fast algorithms
for large-scale genome alignment and comparison, Nucl. Acids Res. 30 (11)
(2002) 2478–2483.
(Source for an algorithm for computing supermaximal repeats easily with
an enhanced suffix array)

T. Kasai, G. Lee, H. Arimura, S. Arikawa, K. Park, Linear-time
longest-common-prefix computation in suffix arrays and its applications,
in: Proc. Annual Symposium on Combinatorial Pattern Matching, in:
Lecture Notes in Computer Science, vol. 2089, Springer-Verlag, Berlin,
2001, pp. 181–192.
(Source for linear time algorithm to simulate suffix tree traversal
using suffix & lcp array)

Understand:

Computation of the lcp-interval tree (Abouelhoda et al. 2004 p. 9)
